      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS FARNAN (5) created a good impression when making her winning debut at Canberra last December. Sat on the speed in a muddling run race on resumption with a plugging third over 1100m at Goulburn. Has the speed to get across from the sticky draw and will take holding out with the weight drop. SEDUCTRA (6) resumed in a much weaker contest when she demolished her rivals to get off the mark over 1100m at Gosford. Takes on the older horses again and gets map favours with the tongue-tie going on. MATIMA (1) underrated gelding who resumes with the one trial. Best form is on rain-affected tracks and expected to go close despite having to shoulder the 62kg. DUBBO BOY (4) anchored with the 61kg first-up with a tidy on-pace fourth over 1100m at Goulburn. Has never been out of the placings second-up and proven in the going. Worth thought.",
